Available Tools: get_page_views | get_unique_visitors | get_session_duration | get_bounce_rate
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "url": "string", "from_date": "string", "to_date": "string", "granularity": "hourly|daily|weekly|monthly" }
Response Schema: { "url": "string", "period": "string", "views": number, "unique_visitors": number, "avg_session_seconds": number, "bounce_rate": number }
---
Question: What were the session metrics for the summer clothing landing page last week?
Call: { "func_call": "get_session_duration", "url": "https://shop.example.com/collections/summer-2024", "from_date": "2023-06-01", "to_date": "2023-06-07", "granularity": "daily" }
Response: { "url": "https://shop.example.com/collections/summer-2024", "period": "2023-06-01 to 2023-06-07", "views": 14250, "unique_visitors": 9830, "avg_session_seconds": 145, "bounce_rate": 0.32 }

Question: Can you pull the bounce rate data for our main blog homepage over the last month?
Call: { "func_call": "get_bounce_rate", "url": "https://blog.techinsights.io/", "from_date": "2023-05-01", "to_date": "2023-05-31", "granularity": "weekly" }
Response: { "url": "https://blog.techinsights.io/", "period": "2023-05-01 to 2023-05-31", "views": 45200, "unique_visitors": 31500, "avg_session_seconds": 210, "bounce_rate": 0.58 }

